a protectorate <span style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% gray;">Washington could</span> afford to <span style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% gray;">meet Japan</span>ese sensibilities <span style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% gray;">with disdain</span>, as it is doing now <span style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% gray;">with respect to the Marines on Okinawa.</span> It is therefore natural that <span style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% gray;">by establishing a true political center the conditions that have kept this </span>dependency <span style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% gray;">relationship going are </span>radically <span style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% gray;">altered.</span>
