es are relatively mild examples of what might be expected if this trend continues. Theoretically, <span style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% yellow;">each new animal or plant extinction</span>, with all its dimly perceived and intertwined affects, <span style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% yellow;">could cause total ecosystem collapse and human extinction. Each new extinction increases the risk of disaster.</span> Like a mechanic removing, one by one, the rivets from an aircraft's wings, <span style="background: none repeat scroll 0% 0% yellow;">[hu]mankind may be edging closer to the abyss.</span>
